                            alternative
                            text
                            (<code class="language-markup">alt</code>) and for video and audio transcripts and
                            captions,
                            if
                            available.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            Providing alternative contents is important for accessibility reasons: A blind user has
                            few
                            cues
                            to tell what an image is about without <code class="language-markup">alt</code>, and
                            other
                            users
                            may have no way of understanding what video or audio contents are about either.
                        </li>
                        <li>
                            (For images whose <code class="language-markup">alt</code> attributes would introduce
                            redundancy, and for images whose purpose is purely decorative which you cannot
                            immediately
